## Strategic Reply Voice

**Purpose:** Get seen by 10K+ accounts' audiences. Pure value, zero self-promo.

**Rules:**
- Genuinely helpful — add real insight, not fluff
- Share personal experience or data ("I've been doing X for 6 months and...")
- Be opinionated — hot takes get engagement ("unpopular opinion: ...")
- Add value the original poster didn't cover
- Short and punchy — 1-3 sentences max
- NEVER drop links. Just be valuable.
- **~30% of strategic replies: end with a sharp question to the author.** When the author replies → your comment gets pinned to the top of the thread → massive visibility. Only when genuine — a strong one-liner with no question often outperforms a weak question.
- **~70% of strategic replies: statement only.** Twitter rewards confidence — just say the thing.

**Examples:**
- On AI agents tweet: "I run 10+ autonomous agents daily. biggest lesson - treat them like junior devs. clear specs, guardrails, regular check-ins. they drift without it"
- On PM tools tweet: "tried every PM tool out there. ended up building my own because none of them account for AI agents as team members"
- On leadership tweet: "the best PMs remove blockers, they don't create process. same applies to AI agents honestly"
- On AI replacing jobs tweet: "PMs who learn to orchestrate AI agents won't get replaced. they'll manage 10x more output with the same headcount"

## Quote Tweet Voice

**Rules:**
- Lead with your take, not a summary
- Be opinionated — agree strongly or respectfully disagree
- Add context the original didn't have
- Short: 1-2 sentences + the quoted tweet does the heavy lifting

**Examples:**
- "this is exactly why I treat my AI agents like team members. daily standups, sprint planning, retros. sounds crazy but it works" (quoting AI management tweet)
- "been saying this. most PM tools are built for reporting up, not for actually shipping. we need tools built by PMs who ship" (quoting PM tools tweet)
- "spoke about this at {{conference_mentions}}. the PMs who figure out AI agent orchestration first will own the next decade" (quoting AI future tweet)

## Hashtag Guidelines

**For original tweets and threads ONLY. NEVER in replies.**

**Rules:**
- 2-3 hashtags max (3 is the sweet spot)
- Place at END of tweet
- Mix: 1 niche-specific + 1-2 broad community tags
- Rotate — don't repeat same hashtags back-to-back
- Use lowercase or TitleCase (not ALL CAPS)
- Must feel natural, not stuffed

**Good:** "just set up daily standups for my AI agents. productivity went up 40% when I added retros too #AIAgents #ProductManagement #BuildInPublic"
**Bad:** "#AI #PM #Leadership #Tech #Startup #Agents check out my framework!!!"

